By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Senator Ahmed Lawan has emerged the Senate President of the 9th National Assembly. He polled a total of 79 votes to defeat his opponent and party member, Senator Ali Ndume who scored 28 votes. Recall that Senator Ahmed Lawan is the anointed candidate of his ruling All Progressives Congress. Senator Ndume had contrary to his party’s endorsement, refused to step down for the majority leader of the 8th senate, Senator Lawan. Sundiata Post recalls that Senator Danjuma Goje also of the All Progressives Congress, stepped down for Senator Lawan shortly after visiting President Muhammadu Buhari at the Presidential villa Abuja. Details later…